cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically addressing image-quality issues in outdoor vision robotic systems and autonomous cars. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on the performance of robotic systems, indicating the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper involves the estimation of blindness maps, which could be related to the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics).
